WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.668
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.205 --> 00:06.872
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.541
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.576 --> 00:11.743
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.845
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.880 --> 00:16.181
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.216 --> 00:17.516
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:19.217
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.252 --> 00:20.853
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:25.625 --> 00:26.491
[ Bells chiming ]

00:26.526 --> 00:28.193
Okay, bros,
here's the plan.

00:28.228 --> 00:29.561
When Chloe's finished
with her lab,

00:29.596 --> 00:31.196
we're gonna run over
and cheer and --

00:31.231 --> 00:32.197
Wait, here she comes!

00:32.232 --> 00:34.766
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:34.801 --> 00:36.268
[ Sighs ]

00:36.303 --> 00:38.170
Chloe!
Yeah, you did it!

00:38.205 --> 00:39.604
-Whoo!
-Guys, stop.

00:39.639 --> 00:42.374
-Chloe! Chloe!
-Guys, please stop.

00:42.409 --> 00:44.443
Guys!

00:44.478 --> 00:46.278
Chloe,
is everything okay?

00:46.313 --> 00:48.246
Uh, thanks
for the enthusiasm,

00:48.281 --> 00:50.415
but I didn't do so hot
on the lab.

00:50.450 --> 00:52.184
[ Gasp ] Oh, no!
[ Kazoo toots sadly ]

00:52.219 --> 00:53.952
But we helped you practice
and everything.

00:53.987 --> 00:55.253
We even wrote you
that song.

00:55.288 --> 00:57.589
♪ You take a beaker
of this thing ♪

00:57.624 --> 00:59.758
♪ And you drip it into
this thing ♪

00:59.793 --> 01:02.761
Both: ♪ When the stuff turns
pink, what have you found? ♪

01:02.796 --> 01:05.630
The equivalence point of
sodium hydroxide. ♪ That ♪

01:05.665 --> 01:07.432
I know, I know.
That wasn't the problem.

01:07.467 --> 01:09.768
It was my teacher,
Professor Lampwick!

01:09.803 --> 01:10.869
He messed me up!

01:10.904 --> 01:12.104
What?
How did he do that?

01:12.139 --> 01:15.273
[ Sighs ]
Well, things started off okay.

01:15.308 --> 01:17.876
15-minute titration?
No problem.

01:17.911 --> 01:19.444
Burets were calibrated.

01:19.479 --> 01:21.146
Base solution measured
to the milliliter.

01:21.181 --> 01:25.117
But then Lampwick came around
the corner to check up on us.

01:25.152 --> 01:27.752
He's just so intimidating!

01:27.787 --> 01:28.820
[ Clock ticking loudly ]

01:28.855 --> 01:29.921
[ Gasps ]

01:29.956 --> 01:31.457
Wha!

01:36.496 --> 01:39.498
[ Beeping ]

01:39.533 --> 01:40.765
Ugh! What?!

01:40.800 --> 01:42.734
No, no, no, no, no!

01:42.769 --> 01:44.803
Too late, Miss Park.

01:44.838 --> 01:48.306
And I failed my lab
right then and there!

01:48.341 --> 01:50.408
Aw, man, Chloe,
that's terrible.

01:50.443 --> 01:52.978
I wish I could go talk to him
about it,

01:53.013 --> 01:54.246
redo it or something.

01:54.281 --> 01:55.480
I know the material!

01:55.515 --> 01:56.681
Wait,
but why can't you?

01:56.716 --> 01:58.517
Nobody ever goes
to talk to Lampwick.

01:58.552 --> 02:00.318
He doesn't even have
office hours.

02:00.353 --> 02:02.287
Come on, now.
He can't be all bad.

02:02.322 --> 02:03.822
He's a man of science,
after all.

02:03.857 --> 02:05.257
[ Clears throat ]

02:05.292 --> 02:06.691
Excuse me, Miss Park.

02:06.726 --> 02:10.095
I realize your time
is not especially valuable,

02:10.130 --> 02:12.030
but mine is.

02:12.065 --> 02:13.598
Now move aside, child.

02:13.633 --> 02:16.001
[ Grunts ]
Sorry, Professor!

02:16.036 --> 02:17.836
Whoa!
That's him, huh?!

02:17.871 --> 02:19.137
What? Aah!

02:19.172 --> 02:21.006
Chloe, you should
ask about the lab.

02:21.041 --> 02:22.941
No way, Grizz!
Did you even see him?

02:22.976 --> 02:24.543
Ah, don't be silly.
Come on.

02:24.578 --> 02:25.710
Sir, hold on!

02:25.745 --> 02:27.979
Um, our friend Chloe
has something to ask you.

02:28.014 --> 02:29.381
Go on, Chloe.

02:29.416 --> 02:31.316
Um, I-I was wondering,
Professor, if, maybe...

02:31.351 --> 02:33.151
[ Sighs ]
Out with it, girl.

02:33.186 --> 02:34.352
I, well...
[ Shuddering ]

02:34.387 --> 02:36.354
Uh, listen, sir,
all Chloe wants

02:36.389 --> 02:39.558
is a chance to pour and drip
that thing again, a redo.

02:39.593 --> 02:42.794
I don't believe
in second chances.

02:42.829 --> 02:44.162
And, frankly, Miss Park,

02:44.197 --> 02:46.665
I'm surprised by your choice
of study group.

02:46.700 --> 02:49.634
I doubt these bears could
even do basic arithmetic.

02:49.669 --> 02:51.870
Can, too!
Th-That's math, right?

02:51.905 --> 02:54.739
[ Sighs ] Miss Park,
my time will not be wasted

02:54.774 --> 02:57.409
on a girl who can't even
start a sentence

02:57.444 --> 03:00.045
or on these bumpkins
she calls friends.

03:00.080 --> 03:02.414
-But -- But...
-Good day.

03:02.449 --> 03:04.816
Oh, man.
- Chloe, you weren't kidding.

03:04.851 --> 03:05.917
That dude is scary.

03:05.952 --> 03:07.586
Ice Bear
slightly intimidated.

03:07.621 --> 03:09.854
[ Sighs ] I'll never be able
to talk to him.

03:09.889 --> 03:12.557
[ Alarm beeps ]
Aah! I'm late for Quantum!

03:12.592 --> 03:14.826
Bye, guys.
Thank you for trying.

03:14.861 --> 03:15.860
Man, poor Chloe.

03:15.895 --> 03:17.062
I feel her, though.

03:17.097 --> 03:19.364
I'd be nervous
around that dingle, too.

03:19.399 --> 03:21.099
Ice Bear
must help Chloe.

03:21.134 --> 03:22.534
Yeah, if only
we could get Chloe

03:22.569 --> 03:24.502
some good face-to-face time
with him.

03:24.537 --> 03:25.837
[ Ding! ]

03:25.872 --> 03:28.307
[ Laughs ]

03:29.776 --> 03:30.942
[ Snoring ]

03:30.977 --> 03:32.444
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

03:33.413 --> 03:35.280
[ Cellphone whooshing ]

03:38.618 --> 03:39.785
What?

03:40.487 --> 03:43.054
[ Knock on door ]
- Chloe: Hey, guys, I'm here!

03:43.089 --> 03:44.556
Um, 'sup, Grizz?

03:44.591 --> 03:46.591
Okay, Chloe,
I got a surprise for you.

03:46.626 --> 03:49.427
[ Chuckles ] Just promise
not to freak out or anything.

03:49.462 --> 03:51.730
Why would I do that?
Come on, come on.

03:51.765 --> 03:52.597
And behold!

03:52.632 --> 03:53.965
What the heck's
going on?

03:54.000 --> 03:56.701
What?! You -- You --
You kidnapped my professor?!

03:56.736 --> 03:59.938
[ Grunting ] What made you
think this was a good idea?!

03:59.973 --> 04:01.206
Hey,
I said don't freak out,

04:01.241 --> 04:02.540
and, heck, isn't this
what you wanted --

04:02.575 --> 04:04.109
some quality time
with your professor?

04:04.144 --> 04:05.143
[ Growls ]

04:05.178 --> 04:06.778
Panda,
how did this happen?

04:06.813 --> 04:09.214
Well, uh, first I Internet
stalked him, found his house,

04:09.249 --> 04:12.450
and I asked him to come with us,
but he got real mad, so I, uh --

04:12.485 --> 04:14.452
Oh, man, that sounds real bad
out loud.

04:14.487 --> 04:16.955
Uh, yeah!
And how about you?!

04:16.990 --> 04:17.956
Ice Bear tied knots.

04:17.991 --> 04:18.957
[ Growls ]

04:18.992 --> 04:20.258
Look,
I appreciate it, guys,

04:20.293 --> 04:22.160
but you could get
in really big trouble.

04:22.195 --> 04:24.562
Professor,
- I'm so, so sorry about this.

04:24.597 --> 04:27.999
So, this is what society
has become, hmm?

04:28.034 --> 04:29.601
And you, Miss Park!

04:29.636 --> 04:33.938
Once free, I will personally
ensure that you are expelled!

04:33.973 --> 04:36.007
[ Screams ]
Okay, Chloe, think, think.

04:36.042 --> 04:38.076
Oh, what to do, what --
[ Cellphone ringing ]

04:38.111 --> 04:39.344
[ Gasps ]
It's his phone!

04:39.379 --> 04:40.512
Uh, uh, I got it.

04:40.547 --> 04:42.814
Let me get in there.
Pardon me.

04:42.849 --> 04:44.015
Oh, okay.
End call.

04:44.050 --> 04:45.784
Peterson: Hello, Lampwick.
Dean Peterson here.

04:45.819 --> 04:48.253
Everything okay?
- You're missing your class.

04:48.288 --> 04:50.322
Just wanted to check in.
Hello? Hello?

04:50.357 --> 04:52.424
Ahem.
[ Deep voice ] This is Lampwick.

04:52.459 --> 04:55.160
I'm feeling ill today --
noxious fumes and all that.

04:55.195 --> 04:56.328
Wait, what?
Lampwick?!

04:56.363 --> 04:57.762
[ Beep ]
[ Sighs ]

04:57.797 --> 05:00.098
[ Normal voice ] Okay,
maybe we just need to try

05:00.133 --> 05:01.566
to just reason this out.

05:02.902 --> 05:05.103
Professor,
please, let's talk.

05:05.138 --> 05:07.005
Talking won't do you
any good now.

05:07.040 --> 05:10.108
I will see to it that you
never roam the halls

05:10.143 --> 05:11.476
of the university again.

05:11.511 --> 05:12.877
Hey, man, not cool!

05:12.912 --> 05:16.181
And the three of you will fare
no better, will you?

05:16.216 --> 05:18.483
A whole family
behind bars.

05:18.518 --> 05:20.719
It'll be life sentences
for all of you.

05:20.754 --> 05:23.355
Aah! I-I can't go to jail.
I'm too cute.

05:23.390 --> 05:24.622
I'll be eaten alive!

05:24.657 --> 05:26.691
Calm yourself.
Okay, huddle up.

05:26.726 --> 05:29.361
I know things look bad --
like, real bad.

05:29.396 --> 05:31.196
But I'm sure we can think
of a way through this.

05:31.231 --> 05:34.299
Please, Grizz! I'll never get a
higher education if I'm in jail.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.468
Okay, okay, how about --
Oh, hypnosis.

05:36.503 --> 05:39.170
-I have a watch.
-Ice Bear can tie more knots.

05:39.205 --> 05:40.705
Panda, any ideas?

05:40.740 --> 05:41.373
Panda?

05:41.408 --> 05:43.208
-Panda?!
-Panda?!

05:43.243 --> 05:45.210
Grizzly: What are you doing?! Well,
he -- he says if I help him,

05:45.245 --> 05:46.711
I might not
have to go to jail!

05:46.746 --> 05:49.514
That's right, boy. Keep untying.
- Yes, sir!

05:49.549 --> 05:50.915
Panda, stop it!
Bro!

05:50.950 --> 05:52.384
No, I don't want to go!

05:52.419 --> 05:53.651
-Get him.
-Aah!

05:53.686 --> 05:55.653
Whoa! Let me go!
No, let go!

05:55.688 --> 05:57.822
-I don't want to go to jail!
-[ Chuckles ]

05:57.857 --> 06:01.059
No movies,
no games, no phone.

06:01.094 --> 06:02.727
He wouldn't last a week.

06:02.762 --> 06:04.229
Ah!
I got to untie him!

06:04.264 --> 06:05.897
I have so much
to live for.

06:05.932 --> 06:07.065
Please, no, Panda!

06:07.100 --> 06:10.102
He's freaking out!
We got to do something.

06:11.971 --> 06:13.104
Panda, comfy?

06:13.139 --> 06:14.572
-Yeah, I'm good.
-I'm sorry.

06:14.607 --> 06:16.708
It's just temporary until
we figure something out.

06:16.743 --> 06:18.743
No, I'm sorry for going
a little nuts there.

06:18.778 --> 06:20.712
Hey, do you think you could
grab my phone?

06:20.747 --> 06:23.281
Maybe I could listen to some
calming tunes or something?

06:23.316 --> 06:24.916
Ah, don't worry.
I got you, bro.

06:24.951 --> 06:27.385
Yeah, Panda, we'll get out
of this, together.

06:27.420 --> 06:28.753
I wouldn't
count on that.

06:28.788 --> 06:30.388
What do you mean,
Lampwick?

06:30.423 --> 06:31.623
Ah, the grizzly.

06:31.658 --> 06:34.359
Unintelligent
but doggedly loyal.

06:34.394 --> 06:36.027
What are you getting at?

06:36.062 --> 06:39.030
Didn't you see how eager he was
to get that phone?

06:39.065 --> 06:42.300
Surely, Miss Park,
- he is calling to turn you in.

06:42.335 --> 06:43.802
Nope, I'm not listening.

06:43.837 --> 06:45.537
-Don't be so naive, Miss Park.
-I'm not listening.

06:45.572 --> 06:47.105
I can't hear you.
La la la la la.

06:47.140 --> 06:50.642
Perhaps he's making a deal
for his brothers to walk free.

06:50.677 --> 06:53.211
Blood is thicker than water,
they say.

06:53.246 --> 06:54.746
Aw, man.
It's gonna rain tomorrow.

06:54.781 --> 06:57.649
What took you so long, Grizz?
Hmm?

06:57.684 --> 06:59.784
Um, what are you talking about?
I had to find it.

06:59.819 --> 07:01.486
It was under Miki-Chan
for some reason.

07:01.521 --> 07:02.620
Uh-huh.

07:02.655 --> 07:05.089
You weren't maybe,
for example,

07:05.124 --> 07:06.558
calling to turn me in?

07:06.593 --> 07:08.426
C-Chloe,
what are you saying?!

07:08.461 --> 07:09.961
It's me,
your friend Grizz!

07:09.996 --> 07:12.263
Would I ever do something
like that?

07:12.298 --> 07:13.532
[ Growls ]

07:14.767 --> 07:16.734
Okay, Chloe,
- this is getting ridiculous.

07:16.769 --> 07:19.103
You're letting him get to you --
like he did to me!

07:19.138 --> 07:21.973
[ Chuckles ]
What a train wreck this is.

07:22.008 --> 07:25.610
First, your friends tie me up,
and now you've tied them up!

07:25.645 --> 07:27.178
Most ironic.

07:27.213 --> 07:28.847
You're next, you know.

07:28.882 --> 07:32.784
What hidden motive lurks behind
his stoic chiseled features?

07:32.819 --> 07:35.687
Do you even
really know him?

07:35.722 --> 07:38.156
Ice Bear
will cut out middle man.

07:40.326 --> 07:42.126
Well, well,
look at this!

07:42.161 --> 07:45.630
No one left to help you,
is there, little girl?

07:45.665 --> 07:47.198
Who can you turn to now?

07:47.233 --> 07:50.935
And, certainly, that feeble mind
of yours won't suffice.

07:50.970 --> 07:53.438
And you call yourself
a child prodigy?

07:53.473 --> 07:57.642
You don't belong in my class or
any class in this institution.

07:57.677 --> 07:59.043
You're no prodigy.

07:59.078 --> 08:00.512
[ Growls ]

08:00.547 --> 08:02.881
I am a prodigy!
And I worked hard for it!

08:02.916 --> 08:05.216
And you're nothing
but a tenured wash-up

08:05.251 --> 08:08.686
who's got nothing better to do
than intimidate and bully!

08:08.721 --> 08:10.388
-[ Gasps ]
-[ Gasps ]

08:10.423 --> 08:11.823
My, my, Miss Park!

08:11.858 --> 08:14.859
This is a side of you
I haven't seen.

08:14.894 --> 08:16.694
Well, can we make a deal
or not?

08:16.729 --> 08:18.029
Hmm.
I'm listening.

08:18.064 --> 08:20.365
Grizz, do you still have
my chemistry set here?

08:20.400 --> 08:21.900
Yeah,
it's in the living room.

08:21.935 --> 08:23.868
All right, Professor,
how about this?

08:23.903 --> 08:26.538
I'll redo my lab
right here, right now.

08:26.573 --> 08:28.740
If I do it right,
you have to leave

08:28.775 --> 08:30.909
and pretend
none of this happened.

08:30.944 --> 08:33.578
And if I fail,
- you can kick me out of school.

08:33.613 --> 08:35.580
And have you all
locked up.

08:36.583 --> 08:38.349
Don't worry, Chloe.
You got this.

08:38.384 --> 08:39.584
We believe in you,
Chloe.

08:39.619 --> 08:41.052
Chloe,
next Marie Curie.

08:41.087 --> 08:42.854
Deal!

08:42.889 --> 08:46.357
Oh, and, Miss Park,
you don't get 15 minutes.

08:46.392 --> 08:47.659
You get five.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.727
But that -- that's imposs--

08:49.762 --> 08:51.362
[ Sighs ]
Fine!

08:51.397 --> 08:53.898
All right, Lampwick,
let's do this.

08:53.933 --> 08:55.900
-It's all you, Chloe!
-Go, Chloe!

08:55.935 --> 08:57.735
Yes, Miss Park.
Impress me.

08:57.770 --> 08:59.938
Your time begins...

08:59.973 --> 09:01.105
now.

09:01.140 --> 09:04.542
Okay, okay.
- 100 millimeters of N-A-O-H.

09:04.577 --> 09:06.911
Record molarity.
Um, um, uh...

09:06.946 --> 09:09.414
Dilute
hydrochloric acid.

09:09.449 --> 09:12.016
Now, uh, set up buret?
Whoa!

09:12.051 --> 09:13.685
♪♪

09:13.720 --> 09:16.521
Ah. Feels like déjà vu,
doesn't it, Miss Park?

09:16.556 --> 09:18.523
You just don't
have it in you.

09:18.558 --> 09:19.958
Ah, which chemical
comes next?

09:19.993 --> 09:23.194
Uh, a few drops of this to --
Ooh. Maybe it was that.

09:23.229 --> 09:26.698
Don't you know the difference
between your acids and bases?

09:26.733 --> 09:28.199
Even wee babies know that.

09:28.234 --> 09:31.402
Oh, but you're no wee baby,
Miss Park.

09:31.437 --> 09:33.771
You're a prodigy,
aren't you?

09:33.806 --> 09:35.440
Come on, focus, Chloe!
Focus!

09:35.475 --> 09:37.108
Getting in your head.
Get out!

09:37.143 --> 09:39.277
Together: ♪ Oh ♪

09:39.312 --> 09:41.746
♪ You take a beaker
of this thing ♪

09:41.781 --> 09:43.615
♪ And you drip it into
this thing ♪

09:43.650 --> 09:46.784
Both: ♪ And when the stuff turns
pink, what have you found? ♪

09:46.819 --> 09:49.053
The concentration
of what's inside.

09:49.088 --> 09:51.155
♪ So I take the tube
of this stuff ♪

09:51.190 --> 09:53.291
♪ And rinse it with
this stuff ♪

09:53.326 --> 09:55.793
♪ I'll just pour
and I'll mix ♪

09:55.828 --> 09:57.462
-♪ You'll swirl ♪
-♪ And you'll drip ♪

09:57.497 --> 10:00.798
♪ And when the stuff turns pink,
what have you found? ♪

10:00.833 --> 10:01.833
Boom!

10:01.868 --> 10:04.435
The equivalence point
of sodium hydroxide.

10:04.470 --> 10:05.837
[ Ticking ]

10:05.872 --> 10:08.439
Whoo-hoo, yeah!
Chloe, you did it!

10:08.474 --> 10:10.942
[ Chuckles ]
I actually did it.

10:12.612 --> 10:14.078
Bravo, Miss Park!

10:14.113 --> 10:18.483
A tad unorthodox, to be sure,
but very well done.

10:18.518 --> 10:20.184
You --
You untied yourself?!

10:20.219 --> 10:22.987
Oh, yes, I've been untied
for some time now.

10:23.022 --> 10:25.957
I wanted to see you perform
under pressure,

10:25.992 --> 10:28.259
and I must say
that you delivered.

10:28.294 --> 10:30.261
I'll count this
as an extra credit.

10:30.296 --> 10:32.130
That should make up
for the lab.

10:32.165 --> 10:34.999
What?! Hang on.
- You're not gonna press charges?

10:35.034 --> 10:37.335
My dear, Miss Park,
do you really think

10:37.370 --> 10:40.438
you're the first student
to kidnap me over a grade?

10:40.473 --> 10:44.509
You are, however,
- the first to get it right.

10:44.544 --> 10:46.477
<i>Auf wiedersehen!</i>

10:46.512 --> 10:49.847
Um, guys, I know things
got kind of crazy in there,

10:49.882 --> 10:51.182
but thank you so much.

10:51.217 --> 10:53.685
You guys are
the best friends ever.

10:53.720 --> 10:55.219
Aw, Chloe,
no problem.

10:55.254 --> 10:57.822
But, uh, you should transfer
to a different class, though.

10:57.857 --> 11:00.692
That man
is truly messed up.

11:04.397 --> 11:07.399
♪♪
